---
// Pistol-range version of BarrelLengthZones (3.0–5.5″+). Includes
// reference-platform tick markers on the gradient bar so readers can map the
// six pistols in this article to a zone at a glance.
// Hand-tuned to the pistol burn-vs-expansion narrative; not directly data-driven.
---
<figure class="pzones-card">
  <h3 class="pzones-title">Barrel Length Zones: 9mm Pistol (3.0″ to 5.5″+)</h3>

  <div
    class="pzones-bar-wrap"
    role="img"
    aria-label="Barrel-length scale from 3.0 to 5.5 inches, with platform markers: Glock 43 at 3.4 inches, Glock 19 at 4.02 inches, Glock 17 at 4.49 inches, CZ Shadow 2 at 4.89 inches, Glock 34 at 5.31 inches."
  >
    <div class="pzones-bar" aria-hidden="true">
      <div class="pzones-bar-fill"></div>
      <div class="pzones-platform" style="left:16%;">
        <div class="pzones-platform-tick"></div>
        <div class="pzones-platform-label">
          <span class="pzones-platform-name">G43</span>
          <span class="pzones-platform-len">3.4″</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="pzones-platform" style="left:40.8%;">
        <div class="pzones-platform-tick"></div>
        <div class="pzones-platform-label">
          <span class="pzones-platform-name">G19</span>
          <span class="pzones-platform-len">4.02″</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="pzones-platform" style="left:59.6%;">
        <div class="pzones-platform-tick"></div>
        <div class="pzones-platform-label">
          <span class="pzones-platform-name">G17</span>
          <span class="pzones-platform-len">4.49″</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="pzones-platform" style="left:75.6%;">
        <div class="pzones-platform-tick"></div>
        <div class="pzones-platform-label">
          <span class="pzones-platform-name">Shadow&nbsp;2</span>
          <span class="pzones-platform-len">4.89″</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="pzones-platform" style="left:92.4%;">
        <div class="pzones-platform-tick"></div>
        <div class="pzones-platform-label">
          <span class="pzones-platform-name">G34</span>
          <span class="pzones-platform-len">5.31″</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="pzones-marks" aria-hidden="true">
    <div class="pzones-mark" style="left:0%;">3.0″</div>
    <div class="pzones-mark" style="left:20%;">3.5″</div>
    <div class="pzones-mark" style="left:40%;">4.0″</div>
    <div class="pzones-mark" style="left:60%;">4.5″</div>
    <div class="pzones-mark" style="left:80%;">5.0″</div>
    <div class="pzones-mark" style="left:100%;">5.5″+</div>
  </div>

  <div class="pzones-grid">
    <div class="pzone red">
      <div class="pzone-label">3.0–3.5″ · SUBCOMPACT</div>
      <div class="pzone-sub">Glock 43, P365, Shield</div>
      <div class="pzone-body">
        Minimal expansion after burn. Muzzle pressure is at its highest. Velocity loss of
        ~55–100 fps vs. a 4.5″ barrel means standard charges may <strong>fail to make Minor PF</strong>.
        Every load feels sharper and louder: not because total momentum is much different, but
        because the pressure-time curve is compressed (higher peak pressure) and uncorking
        pressure is higher.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="pzone amber">
      <div class="pzone-label">3.5–4.2″ · COMPACT</div>
      <div class="pzone-sub">Glock 19 Gen5 MOS, P320 Compact, M&amp;P 2.0 Compact</div>
      <div class="pzone-body">
        The 4.02″ G19 is the most popular pistol barrel in practical shooting. Velocity loss
        is ~20–40 fps vs. a G17. You can make Minor PF with standard charges, but with less
        margin. Muzzle pressure is still high. The difference between fast and slow powder is
        marginally perceptible in flash and report, <strong>but not in felt recoil momentum</strong>.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="pzone green">
      <div class="pzone-label">4.4–5.0″ · FULL SIZE</div>
      <div class="pzone-sub">Glock 17 Gen5 MOS, CZ Shadow 2 OR, MPA DS9 LOC v1/v2</div>
      <div class="pzone-body">
        The sweet spot for pistol competition. The G17's 4.49″, the LOC v2's 4.6″, and the
        Shadow 2's 4.89″ all live here. Comfortable PF margin, slightly lower uncorking
        pressure, slightly longer barrel time. At this barrel length the internal ballistics
        are essentially identical across platforms: <strong>what changes is how much gun mass
        absorbs the impulse</strong>.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="pzone dim">
      <div class="pzone-label">5.0–5.5″+ · COMPETITION LONG SLIDE</div>
      <div class="pzone-sub">Glock 34 Gen5 MOS, full-size 2011s</div>
      <div class="pzone-body">
        The G34's 5.31″ barrel adds ~25–35 fps per inch and a small amount of additional gas
        expansion. Beyond 5.5″ you're adding length and weight for marginal ballistic benefit
        in a pistol. The practical advantage of the G34 over the G17 is the longer sight radius
        and the slightly heavier slide, not a meaningfully different pressure-time curve.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <figcaption class="pzones-curve-note">
    <div class="pzones-curve-title">Why diminishing returns happen fast in a pistol</div>
    <div class="pzones-curve-body">
      Gas expansion follows <strong>P ∝ V<sup>−γ</sup></strong> (adiabatic expansion,
      γ ≈ 1.2–1.25 for combustion gases): the first doubling of expansion volume drops
      pressure by ~55–60%. Every pistol barrel operates <em>before</em> the curve flattens,
      so each additional inch produces a meaningful pressure drop. But no pistol-length
      barrel is long enough for the gas to reach near-atmospheric, which is why every
      pistol load, regardless of barrel length within the 3.5–5.5″ range, exits the
      muzzle with a hot, energetic gas jet.
    </div>
  </figcaption>
</figure>

<style>
  .pzones-card {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 28px 32px;
    margin: 28px 0;
  }
  .pzones-title {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  .pzones-bar-wrap {
    padding-top: 38px;   /* room for platform labels above the bar */
  }
  .pzones-bar {
    position: relative;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .pzones-bar-fill {
    height: 12px;
    border-radius: 6px;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    background:
      linear-gradient(90deg,
        var(--red) 0%,
        var(--red) 12%,
        var(--accent) 28%,
        var(--accent) 48%,
        var(--green) 60%,
        var(--green) 84%,
        var(--text-dim) 100%
      );
  }

  /* Platform tick markers above the gradient bar */
  .pzones-platform {
    position: absolute;
    top: -34px;
    transform: translateX(-50%);
    text-align: center;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 9px;
    line-height: 1.2;
    color: var(--text);
    pointer-events: none;
  }
  .pzones-platform-tick {
    position: absolute;
    bottom: -8px;
    left: 50%;
    transform: translateX(-50%);
    width: 1px;
    height: 14px;
    background: var(--text-dim);
  }
  .pzones-platform-tick::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    bottom: -3px;
    left: 50%;
    transform: translateX(-50%);
    width: 5px;
    height: 5px;
    background: var(--text-bright);
    border-radius: 50%;
  }
  .pzones-platform-label {
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-bright);
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .pzones-platform-name { display: block; }
  .pzones-platform-len {
    display: block;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--text-dim);
  }

  .pzones-marks {
    position: relative;
    height: 14px;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 10px;
    color: var(--text-dim);
  }
  .pzones-mark {
    position: absolute;
    transform: translateX(-50%);
  }
  .pzones-mark:first-child { transform: translateX(0); }
  .pzones-mark:last-child { transform: translateX(-100%); }

  .pzones-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 16px;
  }
  .pzone {
    padding: 16px;
    background: var(--bg-card-alt);
    border-radius: 6px;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--border);
  }
  .pzone.red { border-left-color: var(--red); }
  .pzone.amber { border-left-color: var(--accent); }
  .pzone.green { border-left-color: var(--green); }
  .pzone.dim { border-left-color: var(--text-dim); }
  .pzone-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 2px;
  }
  .pzone.red .pzone-label { color: var(--red); }
  .pzone.amber .pzone-label { color: var(--accent); }
  .pzone.green .pzone-label { color: var(--green); }
  .pzone.dim .pzone-label { color: var(--text-dim); }
  .pzone-sub {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 10px;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    letter-spacing: 0.5px;
  }
  .pzone-body {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .pzone-body strong { color: var(--text); }

  .pzones-curve-note {
    margin-top: 20px;
    padding: 16px 20px;
    border: 1px dashed var(--border);
    border-radius: 6px;
  }
  .pzones-curve-title {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 1.5px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .pzones-curve-body {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .pzones-curve-body strong { color: var(--text); }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .pzones-card { padding: 20px 16px; }
    .pzones-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .pzones-platform-label { font-size: 8px; }
    .pzones-platform { top: -32px; }
  }
</style>
